The zeros of a quadratic are the x values at the x-intercepts of the parabola, where y = 0</ think>
\begin{aligned}\text{Set }y=0\text{ in }y=-\frac19(x-2)^2+1 \\\text{         We get, }-\frac19(x-2)^2+1 &=0 \\\text{         Subtract 1 from both sides: }-\frac19(x-2)^2 &=-1 \\\text{         Multiply both sides by -9: }(x-2)^2&=9 \\\text{        Take the square root of both sides: }x-2&=\pm3\\\text{        The x-intercepts are thus -1 and 5.} \end{aligned}
\begin{aligned}\therefore m-n&=5-(-1) \\\ &=5+1 = 6 \end{aligned}
